Bundle @open-design/host and @open-design/download in the Linux build.

The open-design-v0.8.0 tag added @open-design/download (and retained
@open-design/host) as runtime dependencies of @open-design/desktop, but
tools-pack's INTERNAL_PACKAGES list — the set of workspace packages packed
into file: tarballs and installed into the assembled Electron app — was not
updated to match. The assembled-app production install then resolves those
two private packages against the public npm registry and dies with
ERR_PNPM_FETCH_404 / npm 404, so no Linux AppImage can be produced. Upstream
has no Linux release artifact for 0.7.0 or 0.8.0, so the regression went
unnoticed.

This backports the fix already on the upstream main branch, which adds both
packages to INTERNAL_PACKAGES (their dist/ is built by the root postinstall
that runs during `pnpm install`, so packing picks them up). Drop this patch
once the overlay bumps to a release that ships the fix (>0.8.0).

Upstream: https://github.com/nexu-io/open-design (tools/pack/src/linux.ts)
--- a/tools/pack/src/linux.ts
+++ b/tools/pack/src/linux.ts
@@ -51,6 +51,8 @@
   { directory: "packages/sidecar-proto", name: "@open-design/sidecar-proto" },
   { directory: "packages/sidecar", name: "@open-design/sidecar" },
   { directory: "packages/platform", name: "@open-design/platform" },
+  { directory: "packages/download", name: "@open-design/download" },
+  { directory: "packages/host", name: "@open-design/host" },
   { directory: "packages/agui-adapter", name: "@open-design/agui-adapter" },
   { directory: "packages/plugin-runtime", name: "@open-design/plugin-runtime" },
   { directory: "packages/diagnostics", name: "@open-design/diagnostics" },
